No one talks about how good the Shazam app is. It somehow manages to find even the most obscure songs in seconds. Keeps a library of all songs you Shazamed. It never begs you to buy premium or anything. One of the very, very few things today that just does what it is supposed to.

Doesn't start putting retarded ads in your face whenever you open it and beg for money or ask you to give your email and make an account and other tiresome bullshit. I have used it to Shazam obscure instrumental songs from Asian restaurant playlists with like 2000 views. It works
"Me and my wife actually met on Shazam"
When you both Shazam the same one obscure song it automatically matches you together and sends you each other's location. Started out as an MI6 experiment.
